name: Chestnut-flanked Sparrowhawk
rangeDescription: Nigeria to the congo river basin
description: A tiny hawk with a dark slaty back, an owl-like facial expression, and dense red-brown and gray barring on the breast with redder flanks. These dark colors contrast with the hawk’s yellowish face and legs.

name: Greater Spotted Eagle
rangeDescription: Central eurasia and southern asia; winters to africa, china, and indochina
description: Adults are large and quite uniform dark brown eagles with very broad wings and short tails. Single white

name: Rufous-bellied Mountain Tanager
rangeDescription: Andes of western bolivia and far northwestern argentina (jujuy)
description: Large and distinctive tanager of scrubland, open woodland, and Polylepis in the high Andes form NW Argentina to La Paz, Bolivia. Similar to Saltators, which it was formerly considered part of, but note extensive rufous underparts, and slate gray back and chest.

name: Wetar Scops-Owl
rangeDescription: Wetar (lesser sundas)
description: A fairly common species endemic to the island of Wetar, where the only scops-owl present. Inhabits both primary and degraded forest from lowlands to the hills.

name: Sangihe Lilac Kingfisher
rangeDescription: Rainforest of sangihe and siau islands (northeast of sulawesi)
description: A unique forest kingfisher endemic to Sangihe. Largely pale brown with an eye-catching red bill, a prominent dark mask with pale flecks on its upper border, dark wings, and a rufous tail.

name: Harwood's Spurfowl
rangeDescription: Highlands of central ethiopia
description: A dark, medium-sized francolin with a large patch of red bare skin around the eyes, and a red bill and legs. The blackish feathers of the back, neck, and underparts have pale fringes.

name: Purple Cochoa
rangeDescription: Montane forest of himalayas from northern india (uttarakhand) eastward to western arunachal pradesh and southern assam hills, eastern myanmar, south-central china (southern sichuan and yunnan), northwestern thailand, northern laos, and northern vietnam (northern tonkin)
description: An extremely shy and retiring bird, usually sluggish and difficult to see in well-shaded forests; coloration is unlike that of any typical thrush. At a distance, seems entirely dark with a soft purple crown and tail; up close, black face and wingtips are visible.

name: Blue-headed Hummingbird
rangeDescription: Lesser antilles (mountains of dominica and martinique)
description: A hummingbird of forest openings and edges where it feeds in understory on flowers and insects. The male is splendidly clothed in iridescent deep blue and green.

name: Booted Eagle
rangeDescription: Southern palearctic and sub-saharan africa; winters to india and sri lanka, and southeastern asia
description: A medium-sized buzzard-like raptor but still unmistakably eagle-shaped, with long fingered primary flight feathers, a long square-shaped tail, and feathered legs (boots) prominent when perched. Two color morphs: pale morphs are distinctively two-toned and contrasting, whereas dark birds can be confused with Black Kites and Marsh Harriers.

name: Botha's Lark
rangeDescription: Northeastern south africa (southern mpumalanga and eastern free state)
description: A small, compact lark with a boldly marked face and a small, orange-pink conical bill. Upperparts are gray-brown and underparts pale, with a streaky chest washed yellowish-buff and some diffuse flank streaks.

name: Pollen's Vanga
rangeDescription: Rainforest of northwestern coastal and eastern madagascar
description: Large, black-hooded, big-billed vanga. Males are white below, while females are pale rufous.

name: Forster's Tern
rangeDescription: North america; winters southern usa to costa rica and greater antilles
description: Smaller than all the gulls, with thinner and more pointed bill. Distinguished from other terns by pale whitish wings and orange-based bill in summer, and isolated black ear patch in winter.

name: Corn Crake
rangeDescription: Palearctic; winters mediterranean to africa and madagascar
description: Extremely secretive inhabitant of wet grassland, meadows, and hayfields, mainly in wilder areas. Distinctive song can draw attention, given mainly early and late in the day, also often at night.

name: Mexican Sheartail
rangeDescription: Hills of barranca de naolinco, central veracruz (east-central mexico), and disjunctly in coastal thornscrub and gardens of northwestern to north-central yucatán peninsula (southeastern mexico)
description: Only in Mexico. Fairly common small hummingbird of dry coastal scrub in northern Yucatan Peninsula; also very local in dry scrub of central Veracruz.

name: Damara Red-billed Hornbill
rangeDescription: Central namibia (southern damaraland)
description: Fairly small, slim, long-tailed hornbill. Note the red bill, dark eye, pale face, and heavily spotted back.

name: White-tailed Cisticola
rangeDescription: Southern tanzania (kilombero swamp)
description: A relatively colorful medium-sized, long-tailed cisticola. The center of the tail is blackish, but the tips and edges are white.

name: Henderson Petrel
rangeDescription: Breeds henderson island (southeastern pacific); wintering range unknown
description: A typical uniformly grayish-brown petrel with pale mottling at the base of the bill that gives it a somewhat “frosted” facial appearance. Pale bar along the leading edge of the underwing between the body and elbow is evident in flight.
imageCreditName: Fernando Díaz I Albatross Birding Chile

name: Babar Whistler
rangeDescription: Babar (eastern lesser sundas)
description: A chunky, heavy-billed forest songbird endemic to the island of Babar, located in eastern Indonesia between Timor and the Tanimbar Islands. Male is distinctive, with a black hood, a white throat, bright yellow underside, and dull green upperparts with a golden collar.

name: Rufous-necked Wood-Rail
rangeDescription: Coastal northwestern mexico to trinidad and suriname, and to far northwestern peru
description: Elusive, chickenlike rail of mangroves, less often occurs in freshwater marshes. Slightly smaller than a Common Gallinule.

name: Pink-browed Rosefinch
rangeDescription: Himalayan fir and birch forest from kashmir to southern tibet
description: Graceful medium-sized rosefinch of the Himalayas. Male is bright raspberry pink with a clean “browed” facial pattern and faint streaking on the back.
